         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Dear Sir,— ¶  ¶ I have compared specimens of Bromus Schraderi in the collection of the museum of the garden, and find no characteristic by which they could be specially recognised from B. unioloides, ...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">64.11.00b</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To the Editor of the Australasian</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Letter not found. The text given here is from <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Australasian</seg>, 12 November 1864, p. 9 (B64.11.03). </p>
               </note>Dear Sir,—</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I have compared specimens of <name key="Bromus%20Schraderi">Bromus Schraderi</name> in the collection of the museum of the garden, and find no characteristic by which they could be specially recognised from B. unioloides, the now commonly cultivated so-called prairie grass.<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The Editor commented below the letter: 'This note, with which we have been favoured by the first authority on the subject (Dr. <seg style="">Mueller</seg>), seems to settle the question of the identity of the so-called <name key="Bromus%20Schraderi">Bromus Schraderi</name> and the prairie grass. <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Ed</seg>' </p>
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>M was probably commenting on 'The Schrader Brome', a long article in the previous issue of the <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Australasian</seg>, 5 November 1864, p. 4.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Yours, &amp;c</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>FERD. MUELLER. </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
